Case called at 9:53am [mo]
Defendant Dominick J Delao in court.   DA Susan Happ appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
DA Happ verifies victim rights compliance

The Court gives Mr. Delao his right to counsel and constructive waiver of counsel. 
--Mr. Delao indicates that he does not wish to be represented by an attorney

The Court finds that Mr. Delao is competent to represent himself; and that this waiver is made knowingly and voluntarily.

Mr. Delao indicates that he did NOT receive the State's Pretrial Motions; upon further inquiry of the Court, Mr. Delao indicates that he did receive them at the Jefferson County Jail, but did not review the motions.

Mr. Delao inquires of the Court how to obtain counsel; the Court directs Mr. Delao to apply to the State Public Defender's Office.

On Defendant's Requst to Adjourn
--no objection from the State
--Mr. Delao waives his right to speedy trial

The Court orders that as part of preparation for the Trial and to keep case moving forward, Mr. Delao is to go to the State Public Defender's office this morning, to have determination conducted/schedule a determination appointment. Further, the Court orders that within 24 hours of the SPD office finding Mr. Delao ineligible he is to submit a Petition for Court Appointed Counsel. The Court clarifies to Mr. Deloa that it is not precluding Mr. Delao from hiring his own attorney

The Court does not remove the FSSC and Jury Trial dates at this time.
